 \"-24  78  Link copied!\", \"from\": 952, \"to\": 973, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Share  Link copied!\", \"from\": 975, \"to\": 994, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Share  What would theOlympicsbe without some good old meme-esque content?\", \"from\": 996, \"to\": 1069, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"EnterArno Kammingaof the Netherlands, who competed in the Men's 100m Breaststroke during Day 1 ofswimmingand his \\\"thirst trap\\\" swimshorts.\", \"from\": 1070, \"to\": 1208, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1095, \"end\": 1106, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9996314856277869, \"rank\": 0.00024851750098564074, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Finishing second place did not matter, as he won social media's devoted attention.\", \"from\": 1209, \"to\": 1291, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Competing at theOlympic Games Paris 2024at Paris La Defense Arena on Saturday (July 27) in Nanterre, France, the 28-year-old athlete rocked a tightly fitted, glamorous pair of trunks.\", \"from\": 1295, \"to\": 1478, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1386, \"end\": 1394, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nanterre\", \"score\": 0.9999864998662323, \"rank\": 9.790147940832676e-06, \"text\": \"Nanterre\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nanterre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nanterre\"}, {\"begin\": 1396, \"end\": 1402, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.7749530768196852, \"rank\": 0.25044648507237116, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a decision that was clearly made by a public relations team, the Netherlands has opted for the most flesh-colored orange on the thighs of their trunks,News.co.aureported on Monday (July 29).\", \"from\": 1480, \"to\": 1673, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1548, \"end\": 1559, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9996314856277869, \"rank\": 0.00024851750098564074, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As a result, theswimwearcreated an optical illusion that made Arno appear almost naked, leaving people stunned on social media, as a person wrote on X (formerly known as Twitter): \\\"Definitely watching for the sport.\\\"\", \"from\": 1675, \"to\": 1891, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1737, \"end\": 1741, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arno\", \"score\": 0.9999999084034286, \"rank\": 9.155469085855273e-08, \"text\": \"Arno\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arno\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arno\"}, {\"begin\": 1845, \"end\": 1852, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"score\": 0.9999999979345375, \"rank\": 2.0654162586967765e-09, \"text\": \"Twitter\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Someone commented: \\\"Name???\\\"\", \"from\": 1893, \"to\": 1921, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"IN PUBLIC?\", \"from\": 1923, \"to\": 1934, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"IS THIS LEGAL?\\\"\", \"from\": 1935, \"to\": 1950, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"a separate individual chimed in.\", \"from\": 1951, \"to\": 1983, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dutch swimmer at the 2024 Olympics wearing revealing trunks, smiling by the pool.\", \"from\": 1985, \"to\": 2066, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1985, \"end\": 1990, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9056540870934603, \"rank\": 0.09519105102128492, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Image credits:arnokamminga      A post shared by Arno Kamminga (@arnokamminga)  Up until the 1996 Atlanta Games, swimmers typically wore suits that covered as little of their skin as necessary,NBC Olympicsexplained in February 2024.\", \"from\": 2070, \"to\": 2302, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2119, \"end\": 2132, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arno_Kamminga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Arno Kamminga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arno_Kamminga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arno_Kamminga\"}, {\"begin\": 2263, \"end\": 2266, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.6197760834081889, \"rank\": 0.5928179188962684, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Shaving one's entire body was the primary way to enhance speed through the water.\", \"from\": 2304, \"to\": 2385, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Since then, advancements by manufacturers have created a wholesale change in the looks ofOlympic swimmers.\", \"from\": 2386, \"to\": 2492, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Atlanta marked the beginning of the \\\"bodysuit revolution,\\\" the outlet stated.\", \"from\": 2494, \"to\": 2571, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2494, \"end\": 2501, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"score\": 0.9999796414626738, \"rank\": 2.0302087389448345e-05, \"text\": \"Atlanta\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At those Games, neck-to-knee swimsuits made their Olympic debut, with Speedo's model, the Aquablade, worn by several medal winners.\", \"from\": 2572, \"to\": 2703, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2642, \"end\": 2648, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speedo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1028971346036894e-20, \"text\": \"Speedo\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speedo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speedo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dutch swimmer with a flag at Eiffel Tower during 2024 Olympics.\", \"from\": 2705, \"to\": 2768, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Image credits:arnokamminga  Prior to the 2000 Sydney Games, when swimmers began wearing suits that covered all parts of their body except their feet, hands, and head, some observers felt the suits were performance-enhancing and, therefore, against the rules.\", \"from\": 2772, \"to\": 3030, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A post shared by Arno Kamminga (@arnokamminga)  As perNBC, the World Aquatics, swimming's governing body, declined to ban the suits and, as a result, most competitors inSydneywore some variation of the bodysuit.\", \"from\": 3036, \"to\": 3247, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3053, \"end\": 3066, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arno_Kamminga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Arno Kamminga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arno_Kamminga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arno_Kamminga\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Most gold medalists at the 2004 Games wore Speedo's Fastskin suit.\", \"from\": 3248, \"to\": 3314, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3291, \"end\": 3297, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speedo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1028971346036894e-20, \"text\": \"Speedo\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speedo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speedo\"}, {\"begin\": 3300, \"end\": 3308, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speedo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fastskin\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speedo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speedo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the Beijing Games, Speedo introduced the LZR Racer suit, which was touted as the world's fastest swimsuit, the American broadcaster noted.\", \"from\": 3316, \"to\": 3458, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3339, \"end\": 3345, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speedo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1028971346036894e-20, \"text\": \"Speedo\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speedo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speedo\"}, {\"begin\": 3361, \"end\": 3370, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LZR_Racer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"LZR Racer\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LZR_Racer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LZR_Racer\"}, {\"begin\": 3431, \"end\": 3439, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.99997783906985, \"rank\": 1.9372581994759647e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Made from a compressive, water-repellent, and chlorine-resistant fabric, it was said to reduce drag and provide the most streamlined shape.\", \"from\": 3460, \"to\": 3599, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dutch swimmer at 2024 Olympics wearing striking trunks, surrounded by spectators and preparing to compete.\", \"from\": 3601, \"to\": 3707, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3601, \"end\": 3606, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.91436276143195, \"rank\": 0.08929663711439417, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Image credits:Andre Weening/BSR Agency/Getty Images  The Dutch swimmer finished in second place in his Men's 100m Breaststroke event, recording a time of 59.12,The Spunreported on Sunday (July 28).\", \"from\": 3711, \"to\": 3908, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3739, \"end\": 3742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Birmingham_Sound_Reproducers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"BSR\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Birmingham_Sound_Reproducers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Birmingham_Sound_Reproducers\"}, {\"begin\": 3768, \"end\": 3773, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.91436276143195, \"rank\": 0.08929663711439417, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All jokes aside, Arno expressed his immense disappointment in his result, writing alongside a photograph of himself shared onInstagramduring the competition: \\\"Not what I came for,\\\" with a broken heart emoji.\", \"from\": 3910, \"to\": 4117, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3927, \"end\": 3931, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arno\", \"score\": 0.999999999979309, \"rank\": 2.0067966847549464e-11, \"text\": \"Arno\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arno\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arno\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ahead of the competition, the Katwijk native described a case that saw 23 Chinese swimmers test positive for a banned drug as a \\\"lose-lose situation\\\" while also questioning how the investigation was handled by the authorities ahead of the Olympic Games in Paris.\", \"from\": 4119, \"to\": 4381, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4149, \"end\": 4156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/VV_Katwijk\", \"score\": 0.6862119029616501, \"rank\": 0.44835324812477834, \"text\": \"Katwijk\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/VV_Katwijk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/VV_Katwijk\"}, {\"begin\": 4193, \"end\": 4200, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"score\": 0.9832929895704313, \"rank\": 0.009265495114324318, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\"}, {\"begin\": 4375, \"end\": 4380, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999993510498203, \"rank\": 6.489506650219313e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A post shared by Arno Kamminga (@arnokamminga)    The World Anti-Doping Agency (WADA) confirmed reports in April that 23Chineseswimmers tested positive for trimetazidine, a medication that increases blood flow to the heart, before the Tokyo Olympics in 2020,Reutersreported on July 18.\", \"from\": 4387, \"to\": 4672, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4404, \"end\": 4417, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arno_Kamminga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Arno Kamminga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arno_Kamminga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arno_Kamminga\"}, {\"begin\": 4441, \"end\": 4472, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"World Anti-Doping Agency (WADA)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, WADA reportedly accepted the findings of a Chinese investigation that this was due to substance contamination.\", \"from\": 4674, \"to\": 4793, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4726, \"end\": 4733, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"score\": 0.9645303454266805, \"rank\": 0.02095616959108479, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Arno, who won silver medals at the Tokyo Olympics in the 100m and 200m Breaststroke, said that even if due process was followed, the fact that \\\"they did not tell anyone\\\" about the positive tests until April was a bone of contention.\", \"from\": 4795, \"to\": 5027, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dutch swimmer at the 2024 Olympics in revealing trunks on poolside, sparking viral attention.\", \"from\": 5029, \"to\": 5122, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5029, \"end\": 5034, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"score\": 0.9911157389254404, \"rank\": 0.006797649918150905, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Image credits:itsonlyzach  He toldReuters: \\\"Everyone is questioning it, so it's a lose-lose situation for everyone - for swimming lovers but also for the Chinese swimmers themselves.\", \"from\": 5126, \"to\": 5308, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5280, \"end\": 5287, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"score\": 0.9645303454266805, \"rank\": 0.02095616959108479, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think it's hard to judge or say anything without knowing everything.\\\"\", \"from\": 5310, \"to\": 5382, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The problem is the way in which it was handled.\", \"from\": 5384, \"to\": 5432, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dutch swimmer in revealing trunks at the 2024 Olympics poolside, wearing an orange jacket and swimming cap.\", \"from\": 5434, \"to\": 5541, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5434, \"end\": 5439, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"score\": 0.9911157389254404, \"rank\": 0.006797649918150905, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Image credits: Rene Nijhuis/BSR Agency/Getty Images  \\\"For them to just cover it up, not say anything instead of being upfront and transparent with us, I think that's where the problem lies for most people.\", \"from\": 5545, \"to\": 5750, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5573, \"end\": 5576, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Birmingham_Sound_Reproducers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"BSR\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Birmingham_Sound_Reproducers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Birmingham_Sound_Reproducers\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Whether they are positive or not, I do not know.\", \"from\": 5752, \"to\": 5801, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I can not say anything about it.\", \"from\": 5803, \"to\": 5836, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I hope I can trust WADA that the conclusion was right\\u2026 I am just disappointed in the way it was handled.\\\"\", \"from\": 5837, \"to\": 5942, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dutch swimmer in revealing trunks at the 2024 Olympics poolside, attracting viral attention.\", \"from\": 5944, \"to\": 6036, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5944, \"end\": 5949, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_people\", \"score\": 0.7643218713834858, \"rank\": 0.28588466140406577, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Image credits:Ian_MJ1  While Arno's trunks ignited amusement, other Olympic sports gear drew criticism, as exemplified by Team USA's controversial track and field uniforms.\", \"from\": 6040, \"to\": 6212, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6069, \"end\": 6073, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arno\", \"score\": 0.9999999674785164, \"rank\": 3.2327668737693835e-08, \"text\": \"Arno\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arno\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arno\"}, {\"begin\": 6162, \"end\": 6170, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.5079843027817241, \"rank\": 0.6946655696352209, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The risqu\\u00e9 apparel caused quite a stir back in Aprilafter being unveiled by Nike, with many slamming the decision to adopt the uniforms of sexism and concern over practicality.\", \"from\": 6214, \"to\": 6390, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6290, \"end\": 6294, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/MIM-3_Nike_Ajax\", \"score\": 0.9919148142976506, \"rank\": 0.008143712770638951, \"text\": \"Nike\", \"types\": [\"Q728\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/MIM-3_Nike_Ajax\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/MIM-3_Nike_Ajax\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the time, Lauren Fleshman, a retired US world champion runner, took to herInstagram pageto share her concerns, writing: \\\"I am sorry, but show me one WNBA or NWSL team who would enthusiastically support this kit.\", \"from\": 6392, \"to\": 6606, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6405, \"end\": 6420, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lauren_Fleshman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lauren Fleshman\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lauren_Fleshman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://d